{"parse":{"title":"John Appleby (economist)","pageid":42753003,"revid":794054090,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>\n\n<b>John Appleby</b>, <a href=\"/wiki/Fellow_of_the_Academy_of_Social_Sciences\" title=\"Fellow of the Academy of Social Sciences\">FAcSS</a> is a British economist. He has been chief economist at the <a href=\"/wiki/King%27s_Fund\" title=\"King&#39;s Fund\">King's Fund</a> since 1998.\n</p><p>Appleby has worked in the <a href=\"/wiki/National_Health_Service_(England)\" title=\"National Health Service (England)\">National Health Service</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Birmingham\" title=\"Birmingham\">Birmingham</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/London\" title=\"London\">London</a>, and as senior lecturer at the universities of <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Birmingham\" title=\"University of Birmingham\">Birmingham</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_East_Anglia\" title=\"University of East Anglia\">East Anglia</a>. He is a Visiting Professor at the City Health Economics Centre, <a href=\"/wiki/City_University_London\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"City University London\">City University London</a>. For five years he worked for the National Association of Health Authorities (now the <a href=\"/wiki/NHS_Confederation\" title=\"NHS Confederation\">NHS Confederation</a>) as manager of the Association\u2019s Central Policy Unit.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Astellas_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Astellas-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>   He writes extensively about current health policy matters,including the economic issues associated with the government\u2019s reform agenda for health care such as the expansion of competitive forces in the NHS, <a href=\"/wiki/Patient_choice\" title=\"Patient choice\">patient choice</a>, secondary care payment system, the use of patient reported outcome measures and the measurement of productivity in health care.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>He has acted as an advisor to the UK government and Parliament in various capacities, for example, carrying out a review for Ministers of the future funding needs of <a href=\"/wiki/Northern_Ireland\" title=\"Northern Ireland\">Northern Ireland</a>\u2019s health service, and as a task force member for the <a href=\"/wiki/Michael_Marmot\" title=\"Michael Marmot\">Marmot Commission</a> on health inequalities; a special adviser to the House of Commons Health Select Committee, member of the National Quality Board\u2019s Priorities sub-committee and as a member of the <a href=\"/wiki/Department_of_Health_(United_Kingdom)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Department of Health (United Kingdom)\">Department of Health</a>\u2019s Stakeholder Reference Group on <a href=\"/wiki/Patient_reported_outcome_measures\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Patient reported outcome measures\">patient reported outcome measures</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Astellas_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Astellas-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Honours\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Honours</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Honours\">Honours</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Appleby_(economist)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Honours\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 2016, Appleby was elected a <a href=\"/wiki/Fellow_of_the_Academy_of_Social_Sciences\" title=\"Fellow of the Academy of Social Sciences\">Fellow of the Academy of Social Sciences</a> (FAcSS).<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publications\">Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Appleby_(economist)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Using Patient Reported Outcomes to Improve Health Care with Nancy Devlin and David Parkin, John Wiley &amp; Sons, 2016. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781118948606\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9781118948606\">9781118948606</a>.</li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.kingsfund.org.uk/publications/nhs-productivity-challenge\">The NHS productivity challenge Experience from the front line</a> with Amy Galea, Richard Murray Kings Fund 2014</li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.kingsfund.org.uk/publications/how-health-and-social-care-system-performing-june-2013\">How is the health and social care system performing?</a> with Richard Humphries, James Thompson, Amy Galea Kings Fund June 2013</li>\n<li>The Reorganized National Health Service, with Ruth Levitt, Andrew Wall, Chapman &amp; Hall, 1995</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Appleby_(economist)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Astellas-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Astellas_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Astellas_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20140514183605/http://www.innovationdebate.com/2013-panellists/professor-john-appleby\">\"Astellas Innovation debates: 2013 participants: Professor John Appleby\"</a>. Astellas. 6  November 2013. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.innovationdebate.com/2013-panellists/professor-john-appleby\">the original</a> on 14 May 2014<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">14 May</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Astellas+Innovation+debates%3A+2013+participants%3A+Professor+John+Appleby&amp;rft.pub=Astellas&amp;rft.date=2013-11-06&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.innovationdebate.com%2F2013-panellists%2Fprofessor-john-appleby&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJohn+Appleby+%28economist%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.pieria.co.uk/experts/John_Appleby\">\"John Appleby Chief Economist - The King's F